== Name of park ==

If the park is named for the exploits of John Paulding, Isaac Van Wart and David Williams, surely it should be ''Patriots' Park'', not ''Patriot's Park'': it is not named for one patriot.  I understand that the article is following other sources with this "error", but is there any explanation published as to why this error has been enshrined?  [[User:Kevin McE|Kevin McE]] ([[User talk:Kevin McE|talk]]) 23:38, 23 October 2011 (UTC)
:I agree completely that it's got it wrong (although the memorial does seem to favor Paulding over the others, and properly so since it was because of him that Andr√© was identified as a spy). It's just one of those things that nobody ever bothered to correct, like the spelling of [[Pawling, New York]] (named for someone named ''Pauling'') or [[Beachwood, Ohio]] (someone's misspelling of ''Beechwood''). [[User:Daniel Case|Daniel Case]] ([[User talk:Daniel Case|talk]]) 00:13, 24 October 2011 (UTC)
